content after edit: Next, there is the many-to-many task where both input and output are in the form of sequence data. This task typically refers to most tasks that take one sentence as input and output another sentence. For example, in the machine translation task translating English to Korean, when it receives a sentence in the form of a sequence of words like "I love you" as input, it reads the entire sentence first and then sequentially predicts the corresponding Korean translated sentence word by word, outputting it also in the form of a sequence.

content after edit: Next, there is the many-to-many task where both input and output are in the form of sequence data. This task typically refers to most tasks that take one sentence as input and output another sentence. For example, in the machine translation task translating English to Korean, when it receives a sentence in the form of a sequence of words like "I love you" as input, it reads the entire sentence first and then sequentially predicts the corresponding Korean translated sentence word by word, outputting it also in the form of a sequence.
